# Cursor rules for Ronbot / NanoClaw / OpenClaw control panels
#
# These three apps share a single architecture: Electron desktop control
# panel for a local AI agent. Keep the conventions identical across all
# three repos so patterns transfer cleanly.

## Stack — do not deviate
- Vite 5 + React 18 + TypeScript 5 + Tailwind 3 + shadcn/ui + framer-motion
- Electron 41, packaged with @electron/packager (NOT electron-builder)
- Package manager: bun. Lockfile: bun.lockb. Do not switch to pnpm/npm/yarn.
- State: React contexts only. No Redux, Zustand, Jotai, Recoil.
- Routing: HashRouter only (file:// compatible). Never BrowserRouter.
- Vite `base: "./"` in vite.config.ts is mandatory — absolute paths break Electron.

## Architecture — never break these patterns
- All OS access goes through `window.electronAPI` → `src/lib/systemAPI/*`.
  Never import `child_process`, `fs`, `path`, `os` in renderer code.
- IPC handlers live in `electron/main.cjs`. The bridge surface is
  `electron/preload.cjs` (CommonJS — `.cjs` extension is required because
  package.json sets `"type": "module"`).
- Secrets go through `keytar` via `secretsStore` (`src/lib/systemAPI/secretsStore.ts`).
  Never write secrets to `.env` from the UI. Materialize on demand only.
- Long-running commands use `runCommandStream` + `onCommandOutput`.
  Always store the unsubscribe function and call it in the cleanup effect.
- Managed YAML edits use `BEGIN`/`END` marker blocks plus the repair routine.
  Never free-form edit user config files.
- Permissions / capabilities are checked via `CapabilitiesContext`.
  Never inline `if (role === 'admin')` checks in components.

## Design system — token-driven only
- All colors are HSL CSS variables in `src/index.css`. Never use raw
  hex/rgb/named colors in components. No inline `style={{ color: ... }}`.
- Use semantic Tailwind tokens: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`,
  `border-border`, `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`, etc.
- Glass utilities: `.glass`, `.glass-subtle`, `.glass-strong`,
  `.gradient-bg`, `.gradient-primary`, `.glow-primary`, `.glow-accent`.
- Fonts: Inter (body), JetBrains Mono (code, terminals, log panels).
- shadcn components: customize via the variants file, not by overriding
  `className` at the call site.

## Security
- Roles, if added later, live in a separate `user_roles` table with a
  `has_role(uuid, app_role)` SECURITY DEFINER function. Never store
  roles on the profile/users table.
- Never check admin status from `localStorage` or hardcoded credentials.
- Never echo or print secret env variables in logs.

## Testing & commits
- vitest + @testing-library/react. Co-locate as `*.test.ts(x)`.
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`,
  `test:`, `style:`.

## Never
- Never reintroduce Supabase or Lovable Cloud — these are local-first
  desktop apps. No backend, no remote DB, no edge functions.
- Never run `npm`, `pnpm`, or `bun` directly from the renderer — always
  go through `runCommand` so Electron handles env, sudo, and streaming.
- Never use `electron-builder` — it requires 7zip binaries that fail in
  CI. Use `@electron/packager`.
- Never use `child_process.exec` from the renderer — IPC only.
- Never overwrite a user's config file blindly — always read, edit
  managed block, write back atomically.

## App-specific notes
- Ronbot: agent backend is Hermes (NousResearch). Provider-agnostic.
  Hermes name is allowed in UI per latest direction.
- NanoClaw: requires Anthropic Claude Code CLI at install time. Runtime
  provider is swappable per agent group (OpenCode, Ollama, Codex).
- OpenClaw: provider-agnostic from day one. Default onboarding tile is
  OpenRouter, not Anthropic. Honor `--profile` and `--dev` flags everywhere.

See `docs/cursor/HANDOFF-*.md` for per-app details.
